<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Norway </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministers Support NATO Air Strikes in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1302110794 Oslo Radio Norway International in English 1000 
GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1302110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Oslo Radio Norway International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Norway supports the NATO decision to use air strikes 
in Bosnia if necessary, said Foreign Minister Bjoern Tore Godal, 
but the NATO decision met with opposing views in the Norwegian 
parliament. Defense Minister Joergen Kosmo confirmed, however, 
that Norway is prepared to participate if NATO takes military 
action in Bosnia. Defense Minister Kosmo said also that a plan 
has been made to evacuate the Norwegian UN force in Bosnia, 
should this become necessary. 

</TEXT>

