<F P=100> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air Force Not Equipped for Precision Bombings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1002144094 Brussels DE MORGEN in Dutch 10 Feb 94 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> BR1002144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels DE MORGEN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed KvdB: "Belgian Air Force Not Equipped for </F>
Precision Bombings"] 
  [Text] The Belgian Air Force is not equipped to carry out 
precision bombings on Serbian positions in the hills around 
Sarajevo, an army spokesman stated yesterday. "Our F-16's are 
equipped for bombings, but they are not provided with smart 
weapons, i.e. computer-controlled homing missiles, which 
demonstrated their usefulness during the Gulf war," he explained. 
  "Even if other allies would provide our Air Force with this 
sort of high-tech weapons, it would still be impossible, because 
our pilots are not familiar with these weapons." In recent 
years, the Belgian Air Force mainly specialized in 
reconnaissance and defense missions. 

</TEXT>

