<H3> <TI>   Minister Pronk Hopes To Settle Suriname Aid Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1402085894 Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD in Dutch 9 Feb 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> BR1402085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Senate Ratifying Treaty With </F>
Suriname"] 
  [Excerpt] The Hague -- Development Aid Minister Pronk 
expects that the Netherlands and Suriname will soon settle their 
disputes about the increase of development aid. 
  He told so in the Senate last night. The Senate ratified the 
framework treaty, which strengthens the ties between the 
Netherlands and Suriname in the fields of legal, military, 
diplomatic, cultural, and aid policies. 
  However, Pronk demands from the Suriname Government that a 
Structural Adjustment Program be implemented shortly. As far as 
the verification procedures are concerned, the minister says 
that they can be discussed with Suriname. Pronk also says that 
the restoration of the balance of payments aid which was 
suspended by the Netherlands in June last year without any prior 
consultation, can only be considered if an international 
financial institution supervises Suriname's progress with the 
Adjustment Program. Pronk hopes that he can still reach an 
agreement with Suriname on the increase of aid before the 
elections. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

