<H3> <TI>   First Group of German Troops Leaves Somalia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1302124594 Berlin N-TV in German 1100 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1302124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin N-TV </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] The first 102 German blue helmets left 
Somalia this morning without incident. In Mogadishu harbor, the 
Bundeswehr soldiers boarded the German frigate Cologne, heading 
for Mombasa in the neighboring country of Kenya. From there, 
the German UN soldiers are to start their flight home on 15 
February. The Cologne arrived in Mogadishu under the strictest 
security provisions. The military leadership said that the 
reason for this was that terrorist attacks could not be ruled 
out. 

