<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Liberals Split -- A New Party Is </F>
Born"] 
  [Text] Rome -- The latest split among the Liberals: At the 
end of the party congress, one faction has created the Center 
Union [UDC], with Stefano De Luca as its chairman, and another 
one has set up the Federation of Liberals. "De Luca and the UDC 
are aiming to become a satellite of Forza Italia," Raffaello 
Morelli, vice president of the Federation has said. 

