<F P=100> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Claes Said `Very Happy' With NATO Ultimatum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1002152894 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in 
English 1400 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1002152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Belgian Foreign Affairs Minister Willy Claes is 
very happy with the NATO ultimatum reached last Wednesday [9 
February]. NATO has given the Bosnian Serbs 10 days to lift the 
siege of Sarajevo. According to the minister, the Serbs now have 
no other choice than to retreat from their positions around the 
city by 21 February. Also Belgium is prepared to cooperate with 
possible air strikes, but Minister Claes says he thinks that our 
country will in the first place be asked to offer logistics 
support. [passage omitted] 
  Belgian Foreign Affairs Minister Willy Claes says he is not 
worried about the strong opposition of the Russians. He says 
that it is Moscow that is making a mistake, not NATO. 

</TEXT>

