<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg -- DPA has rejected the reproach of "news 
manipulation" leveled by Defense Minister Volker Ruehe 
(Christian Democratic Union) in a letter to the chief editor. 
He described a DPA report, according to which the strength of 
the Bundeswehr "will probably be reduced to 300,000 men" as 
"completely unfounded." However, the news agency confirmed today 
that it received the information from reliable sources. DPA 
reported that, because of the bad financial situation, it will 
not be possible to keep a strength of 370,000, as agreed between 
Chancellor Helmut Kohl and Former Soviet State President Mikhail 
Gorbachev in the Caucasus. 

