<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Patriotic League Leaders Meet With Russian Ambassador </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1102122894 Helsinki HUFVUDSTADSBLADET in Swedish 10 Feb 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM1102122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HUFVUDSTADSBLADET </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [FINSKA NOTISBYRAN report: "Deryabin Received IKL Leaders"] </F>
  [Text] Russian Ambassador Yuriy Deryabin yesterday 
received the leadership of the Patriotic National League, IKL, 
at the Russian Embassy in Helsinki. The meeting lasted one and 
a half hours and came about as the result of an IKL initiative. 
  IKL is one of the two organizations that Russia demanded 
information about in a note prior to the first round of the 
presidential election. At the meeting the IKL leaders raised 
the subject of the note and the border question. The IKL wants 
to return to Finland the borders fixed in the Peace of Tartu 
[1920]. 
  The IKL leadership was satisfied with the discussion and 
described relations between the embassy and the IKL as 
businesslike. According to representatives of the organization, 
the meeting did not give the impression that Deryabin considers 
the IKL to be illegal or that the organization is in any way 
contrary to the Paris peace agreement. 
  The IKL gave Deryabin a clock made of wood, with an image of 
Finland with borders from the Peace of Tartu. The IKL 
leadership gave assurances that the organization does not 
represent a threat to Russia, nor does it intend to harm 
relations between Finland and Russia. 

</TEXT>

