<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Albania's Serreqi Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1302182194 Athens ET-1 Television Network in Greek 1600 
GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1302182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Albanian Foreign Minister Alfred Serreqi arrived in 
Athens a short while ago. Serreqi will meet Greek Foreign 
Minister Karolos Papoulias tomorrow in the framework of contacts 
between the European Union [EU] and Albania, because Papoulias 
is presiding over the EU Council of Ministers. It is expected 
that the two ministers will also discuss bilateral issues, with 
emphasis on the rights of the Greek minority in North Ipiros and 
on the problem of illegal Albanian immigrants in Greece. 

</TEXT>

