<H3> <TI>   France To Provide $50 Million in Development Loans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1402152594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1440 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1402152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 14 (A.A) -- France will extend 302.2 
million Francs (approximately 51-million dollar) credit to 
Turkey in a bid to finance regions which have priority for 
development, it was reported on Monday [14 February]. 
  Turkey and France ratified a protocol on the issue 
foreseeing 
France's financial support to Turkey. 
  Under the protocol which was published in today's OFFICIAL 
GAZETTE, the credit will be used in Balikesir and Mersin's third 
water purification systems, electrification of 
Divrigi-Iskenderun railway line, in Alanya's small churn water 
purification system and in Istanbul's organized leather industry 
projects. 
  The credit will provide a financial support to purchase 
French-origin items. 

</TEXT>

