<H3> <TI>   Bomb Damages Pro-Kurdish Party Headquarters in Ankara </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1502095294 Paris AFP in English 0826 GMT 15 Feb 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1502095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 15 (AFP) -- An explosion damaged the 
headquarters here of the pro-Kurdish Democracy Party, police 
said Tuesday [15 February]. 
  The overnight explosion, which caused no casualties, was the 
second such attack against the party headquarters since the 
beginning of the year. 
  The Democracy Party has 17 deputies in the 450-seat 
parliament. 
  There were no immediate claims for the attack. 

