<H3> <TI>   Eurasian Metalworkers Federation Established </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1302122794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1302122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] The Eurasian Metalworkers Federation has been 
established by the metalworkers unions of sixteen countries 
including Turkey. 
  Eurasian Metalworkers Federation Chairman Mustafa Ozbek, at 
a 
meeting in Ankara, stressed the importance of establishing 
international social and collaboration organizations during this 
period of political and economic globalization. 
  Turk-Is [Turkish Confederation of Labor] Chairman Bayram 
Meral, stated that the Eurasian Metalworkers Federation will 
contribute to the happiness of the people by organizing work and 
capital distribution among world countries. 
  The Eurasian Metalworkers Federation consists of the 
metalworkers union of Turkey, Azerbaijan, Bulgaria, Kazakhstan, 
Kyrgyzstan, the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus, Hungary, 
Macedonia, Moldova, Uzbekistan, Romania, Russia, Slovenia, 
Tajikistan, Turkmenistan, and Ukraine. 

