<H3> <TI>   Court Explains Reason for Closing Down Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1402155394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1405 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1402155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb.14 (A.A) -- The Constitutional Court 
issued its decision for closing the Freedom and Democracy Party 
(OZDEP) in today's OFFICIAL GAZETTE. 
  The justification of the decision said that, the program of 
OZDEP was stating that "a Kurdish people and other minorities 
exist in Turkey, other than the Turkish nation." 
  The decision said, "mentioning of the solidarity and 
self-determination of peoples in the program, damages the unity 
concept of the Turkish State. 
  "The objectives of the party is similar to those of 
terrorists. 
  "There is a single nation in Turkey and that is the Turkish 
nation.... Citizens of Turkish and Kurdish origin have formed 
the unity of our nation and efforts aiming at separation, are 
being supported by terror," it said. 

</TEXT>

