<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   More F-16's Leave for NATO Base in Italy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1402152494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1420 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1402152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 14 (A.A) -- Turkey on Monday [14 
February] sent eight more F-16 warplanes in a bid to reinforce 
its warplanes stationed in Italy's Ghedi base where NATO forces 
are preparing for a possible air attack of Serb artillery around 
Sarajevo. 
  Ten Turkish F-16 fighting Falcons are already stationed in 
Italy taking part in NATO enforcement of the "no-fly" zone over 
Bosnia- Herzegovina. 
  As Greece did not allow Turkish fighter planes to fly 
through 
its skies, F-16's took a longer route over the Mediterranean to 
reach Italy. 
  The decision of sending the warplanes was made after a NATO 
ultimatum, for Bosnia's Serbs to put heavy weapons in Sarajevo 
under the United Nations control. 

</TEXT>

