<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Justifies Electoral `Alliances' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502214594 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1845 
GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502214594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today at the Quirinale [president's office], 
[Silvio] Berlusconi, the Forza Italia leader, met with President 
Scalfaro for the first time. Scalfaro also met with Italian 
Republican Party [PRI] secretary [Giorgio] La Malfa. 
  Berlusconi told journalists that while his movement was 
viable on its own, out of necessity it was obliged to enter into 
alliances with other parties: i.e. [Umberto] Bossi [Northern 
League], [Gianfranco] Fini [National Alliance-Italian Social 
Movement], and the former Christian Democrats of the Christian 
Democratic Center Party. 
  [Begin Berlusconi recording] Obviously, certain alliances 
can 
result in lost votes. We hope that voters understand, and we 
hope to be able to explain to them that it was in the higher 
interest of the nation that we entered into these alliances, 
along with the need to add to certain lists [of candidates] the 
names of the leaders and protagonists of some movements with 
which we are allied. [sentence as heard]. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

