<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cuba to Pay Reparations to Spanish Nationals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502183294 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1700 GMT 
15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thirty-five years later, some 1,500 Spanish citizens 
will receive reparations for the expropriations that took place 
during the Cuban revolution. The sum of 5.3 billion pesetas was 
approved for reparations today. The money will be paid out by 
the Spanish state, which will in turn be paid back by Fidel 
Castro's regime. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-39385 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu032_l_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-032 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

