<F P=100> SWITZERLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   German Defense Minister Arrives for Two-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1402115994 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 1100 
GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1402115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The German defense minister, Volker Ruehe, has 
arrived in Bern for an official two-day visit to Switzerland. 
Mr. Ruehe was welcomed by his Swiss counterpart, Kaspar 
Villiger. The two ministers will hold talks on bilateral 
security issues and relations with international military 
organizations. They will also discuss international 
peacekeeping operations, the development in Eastern and Central 
Europe, as well as the reorganization of the Armed Forces in 
Germany and Switzerland. On Tuesday [15 February] Mr. Ruehe 
will meet the Swiss foreign minister, Flavio Cotti, and visit a 
Swiss Army regiment. 

</TEXT>

