<H3> <TI>   Ministry Reportedly Cancels Zhirinovskiy Invitation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1502161294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1000 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1502161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, Feb.15 (A.A) -- Russian neo-fascist 
politician Vladimir Zhirinovskiy is not able to visit Turkey for 
the time being, it was reported today. 
  The Russian politician was reportedly supposed visit Turkey 
as the guest of a daily. 
  Sources near to the Liberal Democratic Party led by 
Zhirinovskiy told AA that the Russian politician who had 
reservations at the Turkish Airlines for Monday with a 15-strong 
delegation, could not make the trip because the tickets bought 
by the daily could not reach the Moscow office of the Turkish 
Airlines in due time. 
  However, an official of the daily told AA that the Foreign 
Ministry had not approved of the visit of the Russian politician 
and therefore they have canceled the invitation. 

</TEXT>

