<H3> <TI>   Eleven `Terrorists' Killed, 14 Arrested in Southeast </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1502174094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1450 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1502174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, Feb 15 (A.A) -- Eleven terrorists were 
killed in clashes with security forces in southeastern Mardin 
and Sirnak Provinces, the regional Governor's Office said on 
Tuesday [15 February]. 
  Another fourteen people were also arrested in security 
operations in Diyarbakir, Bitlis, Sirnak and Van Provinces, 
seven of them belonging to a separatist organization, the other 
seven to an outlawed leftist organization. 
  Firearms and ammunition were also seized in a series of 
opertions by security forces in the same area, the statement 
said. 

