<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel: `No Lack of Support' on Bosnia Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1602130794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1155 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1602130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bayerbach (DDP/ADN) -- Federal Foreign Minister 
Klaus Kinkel (FDP) has spoken in favor of continuing to strive 
for a "peaceful solution" for Bosnia-Herzegovina. The decision 
for a military intervention by NATO was not as simple as many 
citizens imagined, Kinkel said today at the Ash Wednesday 
meeting of the FDP in Bayerbach [Bavaria]. In the event of a 
military strike, however, there would be "no lack" of support 
from the German government within the limits of its legal 
possibilities. 

</TEXT>

