<H3> <TI>   Government, Sweden Sign Defense Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1502095694 London HERMES Database in English 11 Feb 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1502095694 </F>
<F P=104>  London HERMES Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Press release issued by the UK Ministry of Defense: </F>
"Rifkind Signs Defence Agreement With Sweden"] 
  [Text] A Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) was signed today 
in Stockholm by Malcolm Rifkind, Secretary of State for Defence, 
and his Swedish counterpart Mr Andres Bjork. 
  The MOU will provide the framework for discussions on 
equipment collaboration and co-operation. Industry will play a 
key role in fulfilling the opportunities offered by the MOU and 
the Ministry of Defence will explore the scope of co-operation 
by investigating defence procurement requirements. 
  The MOU will build upon previous contact between British and 
Swedish Industry and discussions continue between British 
Aerospace and SAAB concerning further development and export of 
JAS 39 light combat aircraft. There may also be opportunities 
for joint development of a new generation medium range air to 
air missile for the Eurofighter 2000 and JAS 39 Grippen as well 
as for subsequent export. 
<H5>  Mr Rifkind said: </H5>
  "This is a very positive step and a number of defence 
requirements which contain areas of similarity are currently 
being considered. There may be more and what this initiative 
will require is innovative action by our respective industries 
to pursue and fully exploit the opportunities offered." 

</TEXT>

